body:
This code:

```rust
use generic_array::{ArrayLength, GenericArray};
use std::hash::{Hash};
use typenum::U2;

#[derive(Copy,Clone,Default,PartialEq,PartialOrd,Hash)]
pub struct Point<Num,AD>(GenericArray<Num, AD>)
    where
    Num: Copy + Default + PartialEq + PartialOrd + Hash,
    AD: ArrayLength<Num> + Copy + Default + PartialEq + PartialOrd + Hash,
    AD::ArrayType: Copy,
    GenericArray<Num, AD>: Copy
;

type Point2D = Point<f64, U2>;

#[derive(Copy,Clone,Default,PartialEq,PartialOrd,Hash)]
struct Vertex2D {
    position: Point2D,
    value: f32,
}
```

produces this error:

```shell
error[E0204]: the trait `Copy` may not be implemented for this type
  --> src/geometry.rs:17:10
   |
17 | #[derive(Copy,Clone,Default,PartialEq,PartialOrd,Hash)]
   |          ^^^^
18 | struct Vertex2D {
19 |     position: Point2D,
   |     ----------------- this field does not implement `Copy`

error: aborting due to previous error
```

The error is, however, that `f64` does not implement `Hash`. This code compiles fine: 

```shell
use generic_array::{ArrayLength, GenericArray};
use typenum::U2;

#[derive(Copy,Clone,Default,PartialEq,PartialOrd)]
pub struct Point<Num,AD>(GenericArray<Num, AD>)
    where
    Num: Copy + Default + PartialEq + PartialOrd,
    AD: ArrayLength<Num> + Copy + Default + PartialEq + PartialOrd,
    AD::ArrayType: Copy,
    GenericArray<Num, AD>: Copy
;

type Point2D = Point<f64, U2>;

#[derive(Copy,Clone,Default,PartialEq,PartialOrd)]
struct Vertex2D {
    position: Point2D,
    value: f32,
}
```

The proper error message here should be that `Point<Num, AD>` requires `Num: Hash` and `f64` does not implement `Hash`, pointing out to the line `type Point2D = Point<f64, U2>`. 

Instead, the error points to the wrong line (`position` inside `Vertex`), and also the reason is wrong. It says that `position` does not implement `Copy`,  but this is not possible because `Point` derives `Copy` and its fields are constrained to derive `Copy` as well, so deriving `Copy` for `Point` cannot fail. This error message is extremely baffling. 

@rkruppe provides the following mwe:

```rust
// try uncommenting the where clause:
#[derive(Copy, Clone)]
struct Foo<T>(T) /*where T: IntoIterator<Item=u8>*/;

fn assert_copy<T: Copy>() {}

fn main() {
    assert_copy::<Foo<i32>>();
}
```
